						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is also extremely fragmentary.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp to the same temple occurring in No. 360 above, by a certain Kumaraśāttaṉ Vāḻavandāṉ Tiruviṟkōlamuḍaiyāṉ Pāriūṉaṉ Maṟṟaṉ of the same place (name lost). Of the <hi rend="italic">Śivabrāhmaṇas</hi> of the temple the name of Śivakkoḻuna-bhaṭṭaṉ Śeṉṉalvaittāṉ of Gautama[gōtra] is preserved.</p>						

						</summary>
